title: Feature/better specification of admixture proportion variables
body:
Changed the "agraph()" function so you do not have to explicitly specify admixture proportions as a separate list but can specify them in the edge list specification.

Code like this:

``` R
leaves <- c("BLK", "PB", "Adm", "Bar", "Chi", "Den", "Ken", "Swe")
inner_nodes <- c("Root", "x", "y", "abc", "ABC", "den", "ken", "she")
edges <- parent_edges(c(
  edge("BLK", "Root"),
  edge("x", "Root"),
  edge("PB", "y"), edge("y", "x"),
  edge("Adm", "ABC"), edge("Bar", "ABC"), edge("Chi", "ABC"), edge("ABC", "abc"),
  admixture_edge("abc", "y", "den"),
  edge("Den", "den"), edge("Ken", "ken"), edge("den", "ken"),
  edge("Swe", "swe"), edge("ken", "swe"), edge("swe", "x")
))

graph1 <- agraph(leaves, inner_nodes, edges,
                admixture_proportions(c(admix_props("abc", "y", "den", "a"))))
```

becomes code like this:

``` R
leaves <- c("BLK", "PB", "Adm", "Bar", "Chi", "Den", "Ken", "Swe")
inner_nodes <- c("Root", "x", "y", "abc", "ABC", "den", "ken", "she")
edges <- parent_edges(c(
  edge("BLK", "Root"),
  edge("x", "Root"),
  edge("PB", "y"), edge("y", "x"),
  edge("Adm", "ABC"), edge("Bar", "ABC"), edge("Chi", "ABC"), edge("ABC", "abc"),
  admixture_edge("abc", "y", "den", "a"),
  edge("Den", "den"), edge("Ken", "ken"), edge("den", "ken"),
  edge("Swe", "swe"), edge("ken", "swe"), edge("swe", "x")
))

graph1 <- agraph(leaves, inner_nodes, edges)
```

Resolves Issue #9.

title: Detailed fitting
body: The fitting function now deals with the admix and the edge variables separately. For this reason, access to the fitted data is destroyed as the environments and such were confusing me; the fit function just returns a list of all the info you could possibly need. In the beginning of fit.R there's some comments with my suggestions and remarks. The fit function is about twice as slow as it easily could be and I'll fix that in a while, but I just thought it's about time for an update now.
